title: Can't Open Links in a Specific Website through Firefox
content: When opening links via Firefox that are associated with the National Association of REALTORS (NAR) website, I keep getting a message on their homepage screen that says, "An Error Has Occurred. An Error Occurred in Client", and I can't go any farther. There's no explanation or "pop-up blocked" notification, just that message. I can open the links in the NAR website via Chrome, but not Firefox. I talked to tech support for the NAR website, but they said they're not familiar with this complaint and said to try opening on Chrome, which I successfully was able to open the link there. Please help as I don't want to switch to Chrome. Is there something in Firefox not allowing it to open? I'm not even sure which topic this falls under, so I picked Accessibility. If it belongs under another topic, please transfer to that dept. Thank you! Annette Karnes
